item.description:
How things changed at the border -
In 2001 when Operation Parakram was launched I was travelling to the Pakistan border. In the train I met a soldier belonging to the Madras Regiment. He started the conversation: &ldquo;Are you an air force pilot?&rdquo;
I laughed. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m flattered you think I&rsquo;m a pilot, but I&rsquo;m just a journalist. He replied: &ldquo;Because of your crew cut I thought you were with the IAF.
